column1: Which team will win the 2018 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Championship?
column4: A team from the Spokane region
column5: ['A team from the Albany region', 'A team from the Kansas City region', 'A team from the Spokane region', 'A team from the Lexington region']
column11: The 2018 NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Championship will be held on 1 April 2018 (NCAA). The names of the regional champions will be substituted in once known. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: Notre Dame is playing Mississippi St in the final. ND beat the best team in the country (UConn). Final is being played in Columbus, OH, which is closer to ND's campus.
Slight edge to Notre Dame mainly based upon power rankings including strength of schedule. Will need to shoot well against Miss. State.
Great Final Four games. Should have read my own previous forecast's comment more closely...
The all-top-seeds final suggests that favorite UConn must execute/play well to win. The most pressure would seem to be on them (to do so).
Notre Dame withstood a challenge from Oregon, and -- as established rivals -- will play tough against UConn.
On paper, Louisville currently has perhaps the "easiest" path to the Final Four at this point, Notre Dame and Miss. St., potentially more difficult. (Though Oregon St. is playing well.)
UConn's recent record in the round of 16: 23-2 (25 straight appearances). Temporary 'bump-up' to their chances for now; will re-evaluate after the weekend games.
It's become a poker table here, so I'm following the all ins (albeit to 95% not 100).
..UConn is powerful but one bad game at the wrong time can still sink them...

UCONN's tam this year may be its most dominant lineup ever. Only Miss St has an outside shot to upset them. But based on UCONN's historic dismantling of St Francis yesterday, I believe a UCONN championship as is close to a lock as one will ever have in sports.
